cs.DC, cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.SY, cs.NI 

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper deals with a formalized, decentralized runtime semantics for a language and framework for modeling distributed object-oriented systems. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also likely as the paper discusses the allocation of computational tasks to nodes to meet certain performance objectives. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is relevant as the paper presents a formalized semantics for a programming language. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper deals with network infrastructure and Quality of Service objectives. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also relevant as the paper incorporates an abstract graph representation of a network infrastructure and discusses minimizing communication and message latency.
